  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for an ML-based surrogate hemolysis prediction model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether a trained neural network surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A multilayer perceptron trained on CFD-derived shear stress and exposure-time data predicts the relative hemolysis index (RH) across operating conditions. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
